      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease a loaf tin and line with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} together until pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} in two additions, alternating with the {{whole-milk}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide and swirl",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Transfer half the batter to a second bowl. Sift the {{cocoa-powder}} over one bowl and fold it in. Spoon the two batters into the tin in alternating dollops. Then ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "marble",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaeh2cu0000kcv432h8yf3k"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " by drawing a skewer through the batters in a figure-of-eight three or four times.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 50 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes, then turn out onto a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
